previous.\nTwenty-five cities in 1929 showed\npermits amounting to $200,000,000 less\nthan in 1928, a reduction of about 10\nper cent and of $226,000,000 below 1927.\nNot all sections of the country ex\nperienced the reaction that took place\nin the metropolitan centers. There\nwere sharp contrasts to this in some\nsmaller States. In Alabama, Colorado,\nConnecticut, lowa, Kansas, Montana,\nNevada, Oklahoma, South Carolina,\nSouth Dakota, Utah and in Wisconsin\nthe 1929 total exceeded by a fair per\n-1 centage that of 1928. This was gen\nerally due to the expansion in one or\ntwo cities in the State. In Connecticut\nthere were big gains previous\nTHE EVENING STAR, WASHINGTON. D. C- SATURDAY. JANUARY 18, 1930.\n\u2014Prer 1929.-. Btoek and 8 alee\u2014\nHigh. Low. Dividend Rate. Add 00. Open. High. Low. Close.\n136 63 Lehman (The) Corp. 23 76% 76% 76% 76%\n23 11% Libby McNeil L... 3 18% 18% 18% 18%\nLiberty Baking Corp. 2 5% 5% 5% 5%\n38% 18 Lion Oil Refln (2)... 6 19 19 19 19\n49% 7% I-iOews Inc deb rts... 1 13% 13% 13% 13%\n67% 28 Lone Star, new (80c) '2 84% 34% 34% 34%\n91 40 Long Island Lt (40c) 2 40 40 40 40\n14% 2% Louisiana Lan A Ex. 13% 3% 3% 3%\n11% Magdalena Syndlcat. 1 Vi\n1 37% 7 Marc Int M(52%c).. 1,10% 10% 10% 10%\n22% 7 Marc WT br sh(62c) 1 12% 12V* 12% 12%\ni 75% 28 Marine Mid Cp (1.20) 6 34% 34% 33% 33%\n11 1 Mavis Bottling 4 11% 11%\n67% 40 Mead-Johnson(t3%) 1 68 68 58 68\n100% 80 MerChap&S pf A6% 1 87 87 87 87\n36% 10 Mer AMf S A (160). 2 16 16 16 16\n61% 18 Middle Wst U(b\u00df%) 6 25% 26% 26% 26%\n42 8 Mo-Kansas Pipe L.. 23 21% 22 21% 22\n48% 35 Morlson Elec (t1)... 4 42% 43% 42% 43V*\n1 33% 5% Municipal Service... 2 8% 8% 8 8\n106% 66% Murphy Co (1.20)... 1 66 66 66 66\n88 6% Nat Aviation 16 9% 9% 9 9%\n48% 5 Natl Fam Strs (1.60) 2 18% 18V* 18% 18%\n49% 10 Natl Fam Spf (2)... 1 25% 25% 25V* 26V*\n64% 10% Nat Investors (new) 14 .12% 12V* 12V* 12V*\n44 20 Nat Pub Sv A (1.60). 1 22% 22% 22V* 22%\n65% 23% Nat Sugar NJ (2)... 1 29 29 29 29\n42% 3% Nat